cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.DL, cs.LG, cs.CY

This paper is about developing a digital infrastructure for discovering language resources, which involves metadata format and dissemination using metadata harvesting protocol. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also discusses the use of web search engines, which suggests a possible fit with cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Additionally, the paper mentions the dissemination of metadata, which could be relevant to cs.DL (Digital Libraries). The paper also discusses the format of linguistic data, which could be relevant to cs.LG (Learning) and cs.CY (Computational Geometry).
